<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-02-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-02-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="349" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d349">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Eustis</persName></hi>.<note n="1" xml:id="d349fn1">Not included in House Document No.
                                225.</note></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-02-05"><hi rend="italic">February 5,
                                        1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Cable me best idea you can form of time when Waller will be actually
                                released.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Olney</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>